  <summary>7/1/1999--Introduced.
Gold Restitution Act of 1999 - Amends the Bretton Woods Agreements Act to prohibit any U.S. director to the International Monetary Fund from voting for any proposal to sell or otherwise convert or liquidate gold, unless the proposal meets specified conditions.</summary>
